
This diagram captures the main entities, their relationships, and key attributes and operations. It focuses on modeling the structural aspects of the system such as `Inhabitant`, `Stay`, `Bed`, `Department`, `Invoice`, etc., along with the core business logic described in your requirement.

---


@startuml

' Entities
class Inhabitant {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  - dateOfBirth: Date
  + register()
  + assessNeeds()
  + acceptProposal()
  + refuseProposal()
}

class Registration {
  - id: String
  - registrationDate: Date
  + submitRegistrationData()
  + saveBasicInformation()
}

class Assessment {
  - id: String
  - assessmentDate: Date
  - needsHelpEating: boolean
  - needsHelpDressing: boolean
  - needsHelpPersonalCare: boolean
  + determineStayType()
}

class StayType {
  <<enumeration>>
  RestHome (RH)
  RestNursingHome (RNH)
  ServiceFlat (SF)
}

class WaitingListEntry {
  - position: Integer
  - waitingSince: Date
  + proposeBed()
  + reAssessStayType()
}

class Department {
  - id: String
  - name: String
  + getAvailableBeds()
}

class Room {
  - id: String
  - departmentId: String
  + getAvailableBeds()
}

class Bed {
  - id: String
  - roomId: String
  - category: StayType
  - price: Double
  + assignToInhabitant()
  + release()
}

class Stay {
  - id: String
  - startDate: Date
  - endDate: Date (optional)
  - suspended: boolean
  - stayType: StayType
  + suspendStay()
  + resumeStay()
  + endStay()
}

class Invoice {
  - id: String
  - issueDate: Date
  - dueDate: Date
  - amount: Double
  - outstandingAmount: Double
  - status: String ("Pending", "Paid")
  + calculateAmount()
  + sendInvoice()
  + applyDiscount()
  + markAsPaid()
}

class Payment {
  - id: String
  - paymentDate: Date
  - amount: Double
  + registerPayment()
  + refundExcess()
}

class CreditNote {
  - id: String
  - issueDate: Date
  - amount: Double
  + createCreditNote()
  + executeRefund()
}

class Complaint {
  - id: String
  - description: String
  - resolved: boolean
  + submitComplaint()
  + resolve()
}

' Relationships
Inhabitant --> "1" Registration : has one
Inhabitant --> "0..*" Assessment : has multiple
Inhabitant --> "0..*" WaitingListEntry : on waiting list
Inhabitant --> "0..*" Stay : has multiple stays
Stay --> "1" Bed : uses
Stay --> "1" StayType : type of
Stay --> "1" Department : located in
Stay --> "1" Invoice : generates
Invoice --> "0..*" Payment : receives
Invoice --> "0..*" CreditNote : may have
Invoice --> "0..*" Complaint : may receive
WaitingListEntry --> "1" StayType : for type
Bed --> "1" StayType : belongs to category
Bed --> "1" Room : located in
Room --> "1" Department : part of

@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes:
- **Enumeration `StayType`** represents the different types of care: RH, RNH, SF.
- **`Inhabitant`** can have **multiple concurrent or suspended stays**.
- **`Invoice`** and **`Payment`** are modeled as classes but note that payments are treated as events in the requirement.
- **`Complaint`** and **`CreditNote`** model post-invoice interactions.
- **`WaitingListEntry`** keeps track of the position and handling of proposals.

